[1
Date: Sat, 29 Jul 2000 21:01:38 -0500
From: "H. Larry Penning" <bevpenn@fgi.net>
Source: Reuters
<http://newsnet.reuters.com/cgi-bin/basketview.cgi?b=rcom:health&s=nN29413774>

El Salvador declares dengue epidemic
------------------------------------
SAN SALVADOR: Health authorities in El Salvador have declared an epidemic
of dengue fever in 5 of the nation's 14 provinces and put the rest of the
tiny country on red alert for the mosquito-borne disease. The disease has
killed 6 children under the age of 10 since January and spread to 595
people, including 102 with the more severe hemorrhagic strain, a Health
Ministry spokesmen said on Saturday. Health Minister Jose Lopez Beltran has
warned that if it is not brought under control, dengue may kill up to 25
people by year's end, the spokesmen said. The 5 provinces declared to have
epidemic levels are San Salvador, La Paz and La Libertad in the center of
the country and Sonsonate and Ahuachapan in the west.
Dengue fever, for which there is no vaccine, causes unbearable muscle and
joint pains, high fevers and severe headaches. In its most potent form,
hemorrhagic dengue, it can cause internal bleeding and death. A 1995
epidemic of dengue fever killed 5 people.
--
H. Larry Penning, MD
Pathologist, retired
